text: The 1995–96 Algerian Championnat National was the 34th season of the Algerian Championnat National since its establishment in 1962. A total of 16 teams contested the league, with JS Kabylie as the defending champions, The Championnat started on September 14, 1995. and ended on August, 1996. ==Team summaries== === Promotion and relegation === Teams promoted from Algerian Division 2 1995-1996 * MO Constantine * NA Hussein Dey * WA Mostaganem Teams relegated to Algerian Division 2 1996-1997 * USM Blida * ASM Oran * JS Bordj Ménaïel ==League table== ==References== ==External links== *1995–96 Algerian Championnat National Algerian Championnat National Championnat National Category:Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1 seasons
